Japan May Challenge Brazil IPI Tax Increase at WTO, Valor Says

-- B y   T e l m a   M a r o t t o
-- 
2011-10-14T12:42:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/japan-may-challenge-brazil-ipi-tax-increase-at-wto-valor-says.html
The Japanese government plans to
challenge Brazil decision to increase the so-called IPI tax for
cars using less than 65 percent of locally-produced parts at a
World Trade Organization’s commission, Valor Economico reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Japan  decided to complain to the WTO’s committee of market
access, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said. The complaint may
lead to trade disputes, Valor said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Telma Marotto in Sao Paulo at 
 tmarotto1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net  